 ## Behavioral Invariants
 
 You MUST implement the following behavioral invariants as named tests first (TDD):
 
-- **immutable valid ruleset**: The accepted sol-usdc-policy.v1 configuration is defensively copied and deeply frozen. (Test: `accepts and freezes sol-usdc-policy.v1`)
-- **monotone threshold order**: A ruleset whose confidence, risk, posture, range, or threshold ordering can relax a higher guard is rejected. (Test: `rejects non-monotone thresholds`)
-- **unambiguous reason precedence**: Every configured machine reason has one unique deterministic order. (Test: `rejects duplicate reason ordering`)
-- **strict deterministic feature binding**: Unsupported feature types or units cannot acquire policy meaning. (Test: `rejects unsupported binding type or unit`)
+- **reproducible generation**: Check mode never writes and succeeds only when every generated artifact matches the authoritative inputs byte-for-byte. (Test: `keeps generated PolicyInsight v1 artifacts reproducible`)
+- **exact schema identity**: The published digest is computed over the exact schema bytes and identifies the documented path and version. (Test: `publishes the exact schema path version and sha256`)
+- **valid public variants**: The fixture corpus contains canonical pair current position current and history success payloads. (Test: `provides pair position and history valid fixtures`)
+- **negative fixture coverage**: Every documented drift class has a named invalid payload with its intended error path and code. (Test: `provides named invalid cases for every documented drift class`)
 
